cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about Neural Machine Translation (NMT), which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for improving NMT performance using back-translation and pseudo-parallel sentence pairs, which involves machine learning techniques such as data augmentation and generation. This makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also uses NMT models, which are based on neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses scientific paper excerpt corpus, which involves image and text processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
